# Integration Guide

## Adding jsprit as a dependency

### Maven
```xml
<dependency>
    <groupId>com.graphhopper</groupId>
    <artifactId>jsprit-core</artifactId>
    <version>2.1.0</version>
</dependency>

<!-- Optional: post-solve analysis tools -->
<dependency>
    <groupId>com.graphhopper</groupId>
    <artifactId>jsprit-analysis</artifactId>
    <version>2.1.0</version>
</dependency>
```

### Gradle
```groovy
implementation 'com.graphhopper:jsprit-core:2.1.0'
implementation 'com.graphhopper:jsprit-analysis:2.1.0'  // optional
```

### Transitive dependencies pulled in
| Library | Version | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `trove4j` | 3.0.3 | High-performance primitive collections |
| `commons-math3` | 3.6.1 | Math utilities |
| `slf4j-api` | 2.0.16 | Logging facade (no backend bundled) |

You must provide an SLF4J backend (e.g. `logback-classic` or `slf4j-simple`) in your app.

---

## Minimal integration pattern

```java
// 1. Build problem
VehicleRoutingProblem vrp = VehicleRoutingProblem.Builder.newInstance()
    .addVehicle(vehicle)
    .addJob(service)
    .build();

// 2. Solve
VehicleRoutingAlgorithm algo = Jsprit.createAlgorithm(vrp);
Collection<VehicleRoutingProblemSolution> solutions = algo.searchSolutions();

// 3. Read result
VehicleRoutingProblemSolution best = Solutions.bestOf(solutions);
for (VehicleRoute route : best.getRoutes()) {
    System.out.println("Vehicle: " + route.getVehicle().getId());
    for (TourActivity act : route.getActivities()) {
        System.out.println("  → " + act.getLocation().getId()
            + " arr=" + act.getArrTime()
            + " end=" + act.getEndTime());
    }
}
```

---

## Providing a custom transport cost matrix

Implement `VehicleRoutingTransportCosts` to supply real distances/times:

```java
public class MyMatrixCosts implements VehicleRoutingTransportCosts {

    private final Map<String, Map<String, Double>> distanceMatrix; // location id → id → cost

    @Override
    public double getTransportCost(Location from, Location to, double departureTime,
                                   Driver driver, Vehicle vehicle) {
        return distanceMatrix.get(from.getId()).get(to.getId());
    }

    @Override
    public double getTransportTime(Location from, Location to, double departureTime,
                                   Driver driver, Vehicle vehicle) {
        return distanceMatrix.get(from.getId()).get(to.getId()); // or separate time matrix
    }

    @Override
    public double getBackwardTransportCost(Location from, Location to, double arrivalTime,
                                           Driver driver, Vehicle vehicle) {
        return getTransportCost(from, to, 0, driver, vehicle);
    }

    @Override
    public double getBackwardTransportTime(Location from, Location to, double arrivalTime,
                                           Driver driver, Vehicle vehicle) {
        return getTransportTime(from, to, 0, driver, vehicle);
    }
}

// Register:
VehicleRoutingProblem vrp = VehicleRoutingProblem.Builder.newInstance()
    .setRoutingCost(new MyMatrixCosts(matrix))
    .addVehicle(...)
    .addJob(...)
    .build();
```

---

## Adding a custom hard constraint

```java
public class MaxStopsConstraint implements HardRouteConstraint {

    private final int maxStops;

    public MaxStopsConstraint(int maxStops) { this.maxStops = maxStops; }

    @Override
    public ConstraintsStatus fulfilled(JobInsertionContext context) {
        int currentStops = context.getRoute().getTourActivities().getJobs().size();
        if (currentStops >= maxStops) return ConstraintsStatus.NOT_FULFILLED;
        return ConstraintsStatus.FULFILLED;
    }
}

// Register:
StateManager stateManager = new StateManager(vrp);
ConstraintManager constraintManager = new ConstraintManager(vrp, stateManager);
constraintManager.addConstraint(new MaxStopsConstraint(5));

VehicleRoutingAlgorithm algo = Jsprit.Builder.newInstance(vrp)
    .addCoreStateAndConstraintStuff()
    .setStateAndConstraintManager(stateManager, constraintManager)
    .buildAlgorithm();
```

For activity-level constraints, implement `HardActivityConstraint` instead and use
`constraintManager.addConstraint(c, ConstraintManager.Priority.CRITICAL)`.

---

## Observing the solve with event listeners

```java
algo.addEventListener(event -> {
    if (event instanceof IterationCompleted ic) {
        System.out.printf("iter %d  best=%.2f%n", ic.getIteration(), ic.getBestCost());
    }
    if (event instanceof AcceptanceDecision ad) {
        System.out.println("accepted=" + ad.isAccepted());
    }
});
```

Available event types (all in `algorithm.listener.events`):
- `AlgorithmStarted` / `AlgorithmEnded`
- `IterationStarted` / `IterationCompleted`
- `StrategySelected` / `StrategyExecuted`
- `AcceptanceDecision`

---

## Providing an initial solution

```java
// Preferred: use SolutionSpec (avoids activity indexing issues)
SolutionSpec spec = SolutionSpec.Builder.newInstance()
    .addRoute(RouteSpec.Builder.newInstance("vehicle-id")
        .addActivity(ActivitySpec.newInstance("job1", ActivityType.SERVICE))
        .addActivity(ActivitySpec.newInstance("job2", ActivityType.SERVICE))
        .build())
    .build();
algo.addInitialSolution(spec);
```

Or pass a pre-built `VehicleRoutingProblemSolution` — but activities must reference the
exact same objects returned by `vrp.getJobActivityFactory()`.

---

## Thread safety

`VehicleRoutingAlgorithm` is **not thread-safe**. To solve multiple problems in parallel,
create a separate instance per thread:

```java
ExecutorService pool = Executors.newFixedThreadPool(4);
for (VehicleRoutingProblem vrp : problems) {
    pool.submit(() -> {
        VehicleRoutingAlgorithm algo = Jsprit.createAlgorithm(vrp);
        return Solutions.bestOf(algo.searchSolutions());
    });
}
```

Alternatively, use the built-in `THREADS` parameter to parallelise *insertion evaluation*
within a single solve (thread-safe internally):
```java
Jsprit.Builder.newInstance(vrp).setProperty(Jsprit.Parameter.THREADS, "4").buildAlgorithm();
```

---

## Using jsprit-analysis

```java
import com.graphhopper.jsprit.analysis.toolbox.StopWatch;
import com.graphhopper.jsprit.analysis.toolbox.SolutionPrinter;

// Print solution summary to stdout
SolutionPrinter.print(vrp, best, SolutionPrinter.Print.VERBOSE);

// Timing
StopWatch stopWatch = new StopWatch();
algo.getAlgorithmListeners().addListener(stopWatch);
// ... run ...
System.out.println("Solved in: " + stopWatch.toString());
```

`jsprit-analysis` only uses the public API of `jsprit-core` — never algorithm internals.

