## Using jsprit-analysis

```java
import com.graphhopper.jsprit.analysis.toolbox.StopWatch;
import com.graphhopper.jsprit.analysis.toolbox.SolutionPrinter;

// Print solution summary to stdout
SolutionPrinter.print(vrp, best, SolutionPrinter.Print.VERBOSE);

// Timing
StopWatch stopWatch = new StopWatch();
algo.getAlgorithmListeners().addListener(stopWatch);
// ... run ...
System.out.println("Solved in: " + stopWatch.toString());
```

`jsprit-analysis` only uses the public API of `jsprit-core` — never algorithm internals.
